protein description: NADH dehydrogenase [ubiquinone] 1 alpha subcomplex subunit 12; Accessory subunit of the mitochondrial membrane respiratory chain NADH dehydrogenase (Complex I), that is believed not to be involved in catalysis. Complex I functions in the transfer of electrons from NADH to the respiratory chain. The immediate electron acceptor for the enzyme is believed to be ubiquinone
Ubiquinol-cytochrome c reductase, complex III subunit VII
Ribosomal protein S16; Belongs to the universal ribosomal protein uS9 family
